<def f='linux-4.14.y/kernel/kthread.c' l='418' ll='433' type='struct task_struct * kthread_create_on_cpu(int (*)(void *) threadfn, void * data, unsigned int cpu, const char * namefmt)'/>
<doc f='linux-4.14.y/kernel/kthread.c' l='407'>/**
 * kthread_create_on_cpu - Create a cpu bound kthread
 * @threadfn: the function to run until signal_pending(current).
 * @data: data ptr for @threadfn.
 * @cpu: The cpu on which the thread should be bound,
 * @namefmt: printf-style name for the thread. Format is restricted
 *	     to &quot;name.*%u&quot;. Code fills in cpu number.
 *
 * Description: This helper function creates and names a kernel thread
 * The thread will be woken and put into park mode.
 */</doc>
